Tapper is a keyboard layout switcher for X Window System and Wayland. Tapper runs in background, when an assigned key is tapped, Tapper activates the corresponding keyboard layout. Tapper key feature is using modifier keys for switching keyboard layouts without losing modifier‚Äôs functionality. Tapper works for GNOME, GNOME Classic, Cinnamon, i3, KDE, LXDE, LXQt, Mate, Ubuntu, Xfce desktops.
A tap means that a single key is pressed and quickly released, so: (1) no other keys are pressed or released at this time, and (2) period between pressing the key and releasing it is shorter than keyboard repeat delay (the amount of time you have to hold down a key before it starts repeating; usually 0.5 second, but it depends on your desktop settings).Ô∏é
